title.narrative: 'By 2020, capacity of the education system strengthened for delivery of quality early childhood education services in rural, pastoralist and displaced communities

description.narrative: UNICEF advocated and provided technical support for the MoE (Ministry of Education) in revising the national Early Childhood Development and Education (ECDE) Policy Framework to guide expansion of services for young children; co-facilitated a national Early Childhood Education (ECE) diagnosis to lay the foundation for developing the ECE strategic operational plans for expanding ECE with quality and supported the development of the O-class Standards and curriculum for quality improvement. | Status:Partially Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020

title.narrative: Availability of appropriate national policy, leadership and budget for early learning (score)

actual.value: 2020:Score 2.5 there is no separate budget line for pre-primary education, let alone adequate budget/funding, and there is no ECE policy, not to mention implementation of ECE policy. In addition, the ECE leadership is still fragmented in the MoE with inadequate coordination.

title.narrative: Share of pre-primary education in the national education budget

actual.value: 2020:Data not available Was expected to reach five per cent, however the data on actual budget allocation were not available at the MoE. The MoE counterparts are trying to tease out the percentage of ECE budget
